Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{for boiling} to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Cut widthways into 1cm pieces.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour.

Once charred, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer to a #bowl{}. Cover to keep warm.

While the courgette chars, pop the pepper onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @linguine{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{10%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Once hot, add the garlic, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and @sugar{1} for the sauce. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, half the @red chilli flakes{1/2%tsp} (use less if you'd prefer things milder) and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}, cooked pasta and roasted pepper until piping hot.

Taste and season again if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

When ready, share the spicy tomato linguine between your #bowls{}.

Top with the charred courgette, crumbled Greek style salad cheese and remaining chilli flakes if you'd like some more heat.

Serve with the @wild rocket{40%g} alongside drizzled with a little @olive oil{}. Enjoy!